### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python application file.
- Implements the web server, routing, and all business logic for the OnlineCourse application.
- Handles reading from and writing to the local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Manages user sessions, page rendering, and data processing for all nine pages.
- Contains functions for enrollment, progress tracking, assignment submission, certificate generation, and profile updates.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each of the nine pages defined in the requirements.
- Each template corresponds to a page and includes the specified elements with their IDs.
- Templates use a templating engine (e.g., Jinja2) to dynamically render user-specific data.

static/css/styles.css
- Contains all CSS styles for the web application to ensure consistent and responsive UI design.

static/js/scripts.js
- Contains JavaScript code for client-side interactivity, such as button actions and form validations.

data/
- Stores all application data in text files as specified.
- Each file corresponds to a data category (users, courses, enrollments, assignments, submissions, certificates).
- The backend reads from and writes to these files to persist application state.
```"

